<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-44-0837 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author describes how operating at reduced throughput, due to the 1984/85miners' strike, was managed at Orgeave coking plant. Problems encounteredincluded gas leakage through cracked brickwork but most eventualitieswere anticipated and prevented so that no long term damage is apparent.Reduced supplies were boosted by recovering as much coal as possiblefrom the stocking ground and operating with many different blends. Themeans of obtaining coal supplies via lorry convoys are discussed andthe effects of pickets and media coverage. 3 figs., 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>